[SN]TITLE[SN]
Abingdon Poundland stabbing: Van driver told suspect to drop knives

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A van driver told a man suspected of stabbing a Poundland customer to death to drop the knives he was carrying.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Ross Overton said he helped an off-duty police officer confront the suspect after he ran from the store in Abingdon on Monday morning.
A 36-year-old man from Abingdon was arrested on suspicion of murder after being Tasered by police as he tried to get into a nearby Spar shop.
A 56-year-old man from Oxford died in the Poundland stabbing.
His identity has not yet been released, but his family has been informed.
Mr Overton, from Evesham, Worcestershire, said he followed the suspect, after hearing "a load of shouting" while making a delivery near the Poundland store in Bury Street shortly after 11:20 GMT.
